Margaret McWade https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Margaret_McWade 0 Margaret McWade (born Margaret May Fish; September 3, 1871 – April 1, 1956) was an American stage and film actress. She began her career in vaudeville in the early 1890s. Her most memorable role was as one of 'The Pixilated Sisters', in which she was in a comedic stage act with actress Margaret Seddon. Later in 1936, they reprised their roles in the movie Mr. Deeds Goes to Town. Margaret_McWade ( born Margaret_May_Fish ; September_3_,_1871 – April_1_,_1956 ) was an_American_stage_and_film_actress .
